<br>
As for my own:<br>
<br>
- Opening more than two bags at a time (if you do any tradeskills, this becomes really irritating).<br>
<br>
- /bazaar is a good idea, but why not take it a step further - player owned vendors.  I want to drop off the stuff I wish to sell and not think about it.  I don't enjoy haggling over pricing or spending hours trying to get rid of something.<br>
<br>
- Command line toggles for:<br>
  a) Looting no drop items without confirmation (if you ever do ML duty in Velk's you know what I mean - maybe something that would take effect as long as you were in the group and would be reset when you left the group)<br>
  b) Loot and Destroy no drop items toggle (same thing, same reason - basically I want an enhanced MLing interface) or something like Ctrl-Alt-Shift-Right Click to destroy if toggle is set.<br>
  c) Do not trade with players and drop items without confirmation (mod rod duty, trying to find spots to click on that don’t initiate a trade with someone, and then digging through your inventory when they cancel - fun).  This would make resetting mod rods rot timers much easier also.<br>
<br>
* These three things affect me every day and are extremely irritating interface limitations.  They do nothing for Verant's bottom line (i.e. they do not take long enough to do to make a difference and are probably easy to fix).<br>
<br>
- Get non no-drop stuff back from my pet.  I'm sitting in US, I win the roll on CC Gauntlets, MLer comes up to me and stands in front of me for a few seconds, then goes and sits back down.  Grats invis Air pet on new CC Gauntlets.  This should never happen.  This is bad interface design.  When you've been leveling for 20 hours straight, it's really easy to give someone something and go down and click that trade button without really paying attention.  /pet drop it *please*<br>
<br>
- Enhanced macro functionality:  Longer and more lines in the macro box (this shouldn't be too difficult to fix and would help a great deal for people who lead raids or try to auction a lot of stuff (who otherwise have to spam the zone with multiple lines of text)); Work as intended (if there are two auction lines one line after another, then they should both be displayed without me having to put a pause between them - the client or the server should accept the commands and time their execution if they wish to do flood protection);  More enhanced language - the ability to make logical decisions based on things like what happens when you cast a spell or perform a tradeskill.  If my CoH spell fizzles, please let me include logic that allows me to cast it again without waiting and spamming my group.<br>
<br>
